The design is clear. Each procedure gets its own fresh `StatementLoweringCompiler` instance (since `SemanticAnalyzer` has `_statementLoweringCompiler` as a shared field). Wait - looking at `SemanticAnalyzer`, there's only one `_statementLoweringCompiler`. This means globals accumulate across procedures. But that's already the existing behavior.

For procedure parameters, I need to:
1. Register param slots as globals BEFORE the body is compiled
2. Emit the actual Pop instructions directly (bypassing StatementLoweringCompiler)

Here's the cleanest solution - add two public methods to `StatementLoweringCompiler`:

```csharp
public int AllocateGlobalSlot(string name) {
    var slot = _nextGlobalSlot++;
    _globalSlots[name] = slot;
    return slot;
}

public void RegisterGlobalSlot(string name, int slot) {
    _globalSlots[name] = slot;
    if (slot >= _nextGlobalSlot) _nextGlobalSlot = slot + 1;
}
```

